<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-AU">
<head>
  {{> head title="Parallel Horizons"}}
</head>
<body class="page-home">
  <header class="home-header">
    <div class="home-header-inner">
      <a class="home-logo" href="/">Parallel Horizons</a>
      <nav class="home-nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/view">Demo gallery</a>
        <a href="/create">Editor</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="home-main">
    <section class="home-hero">
      <p class="home-eyebrow">3D virtual exhibition</p>
      <h1>Build a gallery people can walk through</h1>
      <p class="home-lead">
        Upload your work, organise it on your server, arrange rooms on a floor plan, and share a link.
        Visitors explore in the browser with pointer-lock — no app install.
      </p>
      <div class="home-cta">
        <a class="home-btn home-btn-primary" href="/view">Walk the demo</a>
        <a class="home-btn home-btn-secondary" href="/create">Open editor</a>
      </div>
      <p class="home-note">Signed-in uploads, photo library, and SmugMug integration are Phase 1 — documented in the repository under <code>docs/2026-08-11_phase1_smugmug_and_auth.md</code>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-steps" aria-labelledby="how-heading">
      <h2 id="how-heading">How it works</h2>
      <ol class="home-step-list">
        <li>
          <h3>Curate</h3>
          <p>Upload photos, folder them, and label title, artist, and year. Our database holds structure; SmugMug stores the files.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Layout</h3>
          <p>Activate rooms on a grid, drag art onto walls, set spawn point and wall finish, tune labels.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Publish</h3>
          <p>Share a read-only link. Visitors walk with WASD, mouse-look, and spotlit artwork.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="home-features" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
      <h2 id="features-heading">What’s in the demo today</h2>
      <ul class="home-feature-grid">
        <li>JSON floorplan layout with placards</li>
        <li>Rapier physics and camera-relative movement</li>
        <li>Per-artwork spotlights and procedural wall materials</li>
        <li>Floorplan editor with undo/redo and save-to-preview</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="home-credits">
      <h2>Credits</h2>
      <p>
        Originally from <a href="https://twitter.com/owlsketch">@owlsketch</a>’s WebGL gallery concept.
        David Ma’s Tap Gallery exhibition. Spotlight model by iPoly3D on
        <a href="https://poly.pizza/m/YohOCmn0hO">Poly Pizza</a> (CC0).
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="home-footer">
    <p>Thalia + Three.js</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
